y</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Weapon Skills, dex and my results</span><hr size=1> Well, after getting my ogre beasty to level 15 (yeah I know, this can be achieved in no time flat, but please bare with me) and noticing the complete lack of weapon skills (h2h, 1hb and 1hp were all at 49, which I alternate after each skill gain) I decided to start an iksar and see just how much of a difference 15 points in dex would make (in comparison to the ogre). For this test both offence and defence were maxed out. To add to the mix I added the stats to a level 15 monk that I had made a while ago. <br>
<br>
All classes/races have their newbie quest armor and the rest is filled up with store baught leather for the beasts and cloth for the monk. I know most of you think I should of taken the stats when they were all naked since the monk quest armor is beyond the beast's, but I just thought that it would be more appropriate to do this in the gear that I'd be using when fighting.<br>
<br>
NOTE : The reason I'm doing this test is because I know that with my low weapon skills I'll be missing like crazy later on.<br>
<br>
Ogre (Str 146, Stam 133, Dex 74) - Level 15<br>
HP : 416<br>
AC : 314<br>
Attk : 307<br>
Weapon Skills : 49 out of 80<br>
<br>
Iksar (Str 76, Stam 81, Dex 89) - Level 10<br>
HP : 254<br>
AC : 249<br>
Attk : 178<br>
Weapon Skills : 41 out of 55<br>
<br>
Human Monk (Str 80, Stam 126, Dex 85) - Level 15<br>
HP : 389<br>
AC : 298<br>
Attk : 317<br>
Weapon Skills : 80 (maxed)<br>
<br>
As you can see, the monk has a highest attk because of his maxed out weapon skills. There's only 1 reason for this and that's because he's only got 2 skills to raise at the same time (h2h and 1hb) unlike beastlords which need to raise 3 (that's IF you want to keep all skills maxed).<br>
<br>
The ogre isn't very far behind the monk in the attk section, he pretty much wins in everything else. The only reason for this is because of his high str. Imagine how high his attk would be if his weapon skills were actually maxed out? From what I've seen, I gain about 2.5 in attk for every skill again that I get from a weapon skill. So with a rough estimate, my attk would be around 384 if my skills were maxed out (which would be insanely awesome). But at this rate, I don't see it happening anytime soon (not even until I get into my mid 40s.) <br>
<br>
Up until level 8, I had the iksar's weapon skills all maxed out. I was really suprised with how well this was going and was thinking of scratching my ogre for him (also for the killer regen). With only 1 blue left until level 11, my skills are already starting to lack. There's no point for me to even continue the iksar because his attk will be lower then that of the ogre's because of his very much lower strenght (we're talking a 66 point difference if you add the str buff to him) and the fact that his weapon skills won't get maxed for a while.<br>
<br>
With these results in mind, I'm either going to be dropping 1hb or 1hp so I could try and get better weapon skills. Heck, I might just drop both and only keep h2h. If I can get that skill maxed out I'll be without a doubt hitting a lot more. Even though the only affordable h2h weapon is the polished steel ulak (and the fact that I play on Kane Bayle, the newly opened server, which makes it incredibly difficult to get some of the better h2h), I could still see myself doing more damage then with, let's say, a fighting baton (8/20) and a crystalline spider fang (10/22) that have a skill which wouldn't even be half way to being maxed. I could always opt to just cast fleeting flury every fight and getting myself a bunch of dex gear, but my point in mind is to be as efficient as possible and sacrificing AC/HP gear for that skill seems unfeasable.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I just thought that since I've been reading pretty much every post made on these boards that I should be giving back to the community. <p><font COLOR=0000DD>
